New York Jets Waive Defensive End Gholston, Release Tight End Ben Hartsock

-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 
2011-03-03T05:01:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-03/defensive-end-gholston-tight-end-hartsock-dropped-by-new-york-jets.html
Defensive end Vernon Gholston was
waived and tight end Ben Hartsock was released yesterday by the  New York Jets , General Manager Mike Tannenbaum said.  Gholston, 24, a Jets first-round draft pick in 2008, spent
three seasons with the National Football League team. He played
in 45 regular-season games, recording 32 tackles and 23 special
teams stops.  Hartsock, 30, joined the Jets as a free agent in 2009 after
being released by the Atlanta Falcons. In his two seasons with
the Jets, he appeared in all 32 regular-season games and six
postseason contests. He also has played for the Tennessee Titans
and  Indianapolis Colts .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
 nkercheval@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at 
 msillup@bloomberg.net  